James Rising engaged in crafting email responses for prospective students of various environmental policy programs. The discussion included formulating a gentle rejection message for students unable to secure funding, outlining alternative financial opportunities. Next, a follow-up email was constructed for self-funding students, encouraging them to submit their CVs for faculty review within a week. Finally, a message was drafted for prospective PhD students who have secured fellowships or grants, inviting them to apply and highlighting the importance of connecting their funding to relevant research interests.
